A man was left critically injured when a motorbike t-boned an SUV on the R563 near Hekpoort, west of Johannesburg on Sunday.Paramedics found the SUV and motorbike in the middle of the road. And the body of the biker was found lying in the front of the SUV while the driver was found walking around on the scene.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said &#8220;The biker was found to have sustained murderous injuries and was also found to be in a critical condition. Treatment and advanced life support interventions were immediately performed on the patient in an effort to stabilise his vital signs&#8221;.Meiring added &#8220;the man was airlifted by a private medical helicopter to a private hospital in Johannesburg for urgent treatment&#8221;.The driver of the SUV was assessed and found to have escaped injury.it is believed that the SUV turned in front of the motorbike. The biker was unable to swerve in time.-TNA Reporter 